title: Voter turnout in UK elections 1918 to 2019
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Voter turnout, containing a total of 29 data points.
In general Voter turnout has rose over the Year.
The most drastic increase took place within the Year 1918 and 1922.
The highest Voter turnout, of value 83.9 was reached at Year 1950
The lowest Voter turnout, of value 57.2 was reported at Year 1918
